@node "Installation" "Installation               "
@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

Installation is easy:  Just copy the complete drawer anywhere you want it.  That's all; however, you'll need at least @{"MUI 3.1" link MUI}.  MUI can be found e.g. on Aminet in misc/libs.
The settings are done by the MUI preferences program as usual.  Some things, like the colour of the stones, are adjustable in MUIReversi.  See @{"configuration" link "Configuration" 0} for more details.

@{b}REMOVING THE WHOLE THING@{ub}

First of all, remove the MUIReversi drawer.  As with all MUI programs, there are also some files left in ENVARC:  

    envarc:MUIReversi.cfg
    envarc:MUI/reversi.?.cfg
    envarc:MUI/reversi.?.cfg.error
    envarc:MUI/reversi.?.wini
    envarc:MUI/reversi.?.wini.error

You'll have to delete these by hand.
@endnode

