@node "Configuration" "Configuration"
@{b}THE MENU CONFIGURATION@{ub}

Since this a @{"MUI" link "MUI"} application, nearly the whole appearance can be adjusted.  See your MUI documentation for more info about this.  Just for your info:  The board uses the background of a group.  

The rest is configurable via the Configuration menu:

       @{"Game Variant..." link "Game Variant" 0}   (Amiga-V)
       @{"Computer...    " link "Computer" 0}   (Amiga-C)
       @{"Colors...      " link "Colors" 0}   (Amiga-F)
       @{"MUI...         " link "mui:docs/englisch/MUI.guide/main" 0}

The first three items all open the same MUIReversi window and display the appropriate group.  
The last item opens the @{"MUI-Preferences" link "mui:docs/englisch/MUI.guide/main" 0} to alter the local appearance settings of MUIReversi.  If enabled, the small gadget with the MUI logo in the upper right corner of the windows will do the same.  

All settings will be saved in the ENV: and ENVARC: drawers on program exit.

To close the configuration window, press either
 @{"     OK      " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{" New Game " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{"   Cancel   " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}
@endnode

@node "Game Variant" "Variants"
@next "Computer"
@{b}THE VARIANT SETTINGS@{ub}

This Reversi version allows you to adjust several rules of the game:

  @{"the rows per move" link "Rows_per_Move" 0}
  @{"the size of the board" link "Board_Size" 0}
  @{"the start positions" link "Game_Start" 0}

The default configuration is:
  - turn all rows per move
  - size of the board is 8x8
  - start with the stones placed diagonally

To close the configuration window, press either
 @{"     OK      " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{" New Game " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{"   Cancel   " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}
@endnode

@node "Computer" "Computer Opponent"
@{b}THE COMPUTER OPPONENT SETTINGS@{ub}

No computer game is complete without a good opponent played by the computer.  In this window you can adjust your ultimate nightmare in playing Reversi.  

                 Human - Human
                 Human - Computer
              Computer - Human
              Computer - Computer

You can adjust the computer's intelligence in 3 levels.  Level 1 is the easiest - the time needed to compute the next move is short even on slow machines.  Level 3 is the hardest, and also the most time consuming.  Using huge boards on slow Amigas with this level might cost you your nerves. :)  
The @{"rows per move" link "" 0} setting will also affect the computers speed.  "turn all rows per move" is the fastest, while "turn any rows per move" will again let your computer brood for a while; however, this is also the most interesting version, since you have a maximum of freedom in your moves.  

To close the configuration window, press either
 @{"     OK      " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{" New Game " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}  @{"   Cancel   " link "Config_EndButtons" 0}
@endnode

